  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. Key International Legislation\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Wolfsberg Principles\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Directives\n\n2. Typical Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping\n- Risk assessment\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n3. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Financial Intelligence Units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n\n5. Key Compliance Obligations\n- Identifying suspicious transactions\n- Verifying customer identities\n- Implementing robust internal controls\n- Conducting regular risk assessments\n- Training employees on AML procedures\n\n6. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have varying specific regulations\n- Complexity increases with cross-border transactions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent financial crimes and ensure transparency in financial systems.",
